Package: autobeale
Type: Package
Title: autobeale: code to calculate loads by means of Beale's Ratio Estimator.
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c( person("Steve", "Westenbroek", role = c("aut","cre"),
    email = "smwesten@usgs.gov"),
    person("Rem","Confessor", role = c("ctb"),
    email = "rconfeso@heidelberg.edu"),
    person("Peter","Richards", role=c("aut"),
    email = "prichard@heidelberg.edu") )
Description:
    This package is an updated version of AutoBeale, a Fortran program aimed at programmatically
    partitioning flow and concentration data into stratums in such a way as to minimize the overall
    root-mean squared error in the overall load estimate. 
License: CC0
Depends: R (>= 3.0)
Imports:
    R6,
    mcga,
    dplyr,
    lubridate (>= 1.5.0)
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
